rComments: Attention perspective students, if you consider taking classes with her this is a huge mistake. People reported her for academic bullying and discrimination. If you still decide to take her class make sure you check all her rules. Some are usually contrary to the universitys policy.

She's nice as a person, but lacks a lot when it comes to teaching. She's prone to unexpected bouts of frustration and bitterness for those who have a hard time understanding advanced grammar, and tends to exacerbate issues in place of resolving them (this is a 4th year course mind you). One of the hardest classes I've ever taken, hands down.
WORST PROFESSOR. I dropped Linguistics as a major because of her!
Incredibly meticulous with the material. That can be a turnoff for some, but an inspiration for others.

rComments: Assignments were challenging. This course requires a lot of self study and practice. However, it is very doable! Cuervo's lectures were super helpful and clear.
Challenging assignments. She's really nice and helpful though!!

Terrible. Slides are very not helpful, read the wholeeee book and try to understand it, even though she makes syntax super hard.. and gives super hard assignments which you can never find answers from the book...she claims that you should use your own brain.....good luck for those who cannot drop it
One of the worst teachers that I have ever had. Do not ever take syntax with her.

So far, a very effective and thorough professor. She uses good examples and makes excellent use of her visuals during lecture despite the fact that a lot of information often needs to be crammed within the threshold of two hours. She is fair enough to post lectures online, and had the (in my opinion) brilliant idea of weekly tests.
Very helpful, knowledgeable, and organized.

Syntax with her is just hell. She can't teach! She talks AT the class and uses way too much powerpoint. Posting the slides IS helpful, but she should draw on a board to show us step by step how to do things! Syntax is pretty mathematical but she blabs in such a disorganized manner! Has no clue where the students stand and picks the WORST TA ever!

The material was very hard, despite which I got a B+ in the course from studying hard.  Cuervo is by far the worst language teacher I have had.  She provided me with the answers to the term test after asking her.  A prof should post clear, concise test solutions on his/her website and/or distribute such solutions in class.

This prof holds grudges against students for very silly reasons. Grades according to who she likes best, particularly for participation. Actual participation and quality of comments does not matter. Fortunately, the TA graded several assignments allowing the students that she didn't like to still recieve good grades.

Cuervo is amazing, very helpful and funny! Please, don't anyone be put off by the other comments here. As they've stated, they did poorly in the class, and  want to blame it on the prof (because they're mature like that) Cuervo is fabulous!!!
